<div id="review_1291864001" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1291864001" />
    <a title="Stephanie Daley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36352582-stephanie-daley"><img alt="Stephanie Daley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642204818p2/36352582.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1291864001?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephanie Daley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephanie Daley" href="/user/show/36352582-stephanie-daley">Stephanie Daley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1291864001" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13043360895085483005">I love anthologies and this one...wow..never have I loved and liked EVERY book put into an anthology! Every book was different and wonderful in their own way. The best thing about anthologies is that you normally find a couple of new authors to follow..I have found 14 new authors for me and 1 to love even more than i do already. Spectacular line up!<br/><br/> I am also leaving reviews for each individual book as well with the link to them (if applicable) ..since I read the book I should leave my review wi</span>
  <span id="freeText13043360895085483005" style="display:none">I love anthologies and this one...wow..never have I loved and liked EVERY book put into an anthology! Every book was different and wonderful in their own way. The best thing about anthologies is that you normally find a couple of new authors to follow..I have found 14 new authors for me and 1 to love even more than i do already. Spectacular line up!<br /><br /> I am also leaving reviews for each individual book as well with the link to them (if applicable) ..since I read the book I should leave my review with it as well♡...<br /><br />Royal Blood (Royal Blood #1) -by Amity Cross ~5 Stars~<br />This book was dark, raw, and explosive and Amity Cross just got her own collection on my kindle! <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1STSVwt">http://bit.ly/1STSVwt</a><br /><br />Angel Falling (Falling #1) - by Audrey Carlan ~4 Stars~<br />I think this was a pretty good read. It had a nice flow to it and some drama, love, and humor. <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1STSQZt">http://bit.ly/1STSQZt</a><br /><br />Escaping Me - by Cat Mason ~5 Stars~<br />This was really good! Very different from what I normally read and it was a nice change. Very hot! <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1STSGBx">http://bit.ly/1STSGBx</a> <br /><br />Releasing Rage - by Cynthia Sax ~5 Stars~<br />I don't read too much Sci-fi but Releasing Rage by Cynthia Sax was awesome and I will definitely be reading more from her…<br /><br />My Last Dom - By: Deanndra Hall ~5 Stars~<br />Wow..not what I expected from the title and there is more to this story than just kink.. amazing read<br /><br />Perpetual Love - By: Jamie Salisbury ~4 Stars~<br />If you like old fashioned romance then this book is for you.<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1BI6Z1b">http://bit.ly/1BI6Z1b</a><br /><br />Letting Go (Anchored Hearts #1) by J.M. Witt ~5 Stars~<br />The story line is not overly dramatic and I found it very entertaining. I will definitely keep reading from this author! <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1AVtswA">http://bit.ly/1AVtswA</a><br /><br /> The Descendant (The Descendant Vampire #1)~5 stars~<br />by Kelley Grealis<br />Wow! This was an awesome take on vampires and I loved it! There was plenty of what the?? &amp; No ways!! in this book. Definitely reading more from this author and I have to read the rest of this series! <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1B2kvSC">http://bit.ly/1B2kvSC</a><br /><br />Rescued (Three's Allowed, #2) ~4 stars~<br />by Laura Harner<br />This was a really good read! I definitely will be reading more from this author. There a great thrill, sexiness, and drama. <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1B2kAWg">http://bit.ly/1B2kAWg</a><br /><br />Man On (Black Jack Gentlemen, #1) ~5 stars~<br />by Liz Crowe <br />I loved this book! I have really never read anything like this and I am glad that i did because I want to read more from this author. <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1IRF4nr">http://bit.ly/1IRF4nr</a><br /><br />Relent (Sydney Storm MC, #1) ~5 stars~<br />by Nina Levine <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1IRE6Yn">http://bit.ly/1IRE6Yn</a><br />The characters were awesome, sexy, and hot! The drama was not overloaded and just mixed well with the plot. I cannot wait to read more from Nina Levine!<br /><br />Make Mine a Cowboy (Cowboy Dreamin', #1) ~5 stars~<br />by Sandy Sullivan<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1J3KAn6">http://bit.ly/1J3KAn6</a> I really loved this book! It was an easy read and flow that I was so sad when it was finished, but that is good for the author because I will definitely be checking out more of her books! Perfect amount of steam, drama, romance, and humor!<br /><br />SEAL Under Covers (SEAL Brotherhood #3)~5 stars~ <br />by Sharon Hamilton <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1QFRdQL">http://bit.ly/1QFRdQL</a><br />Hot! Very good read and I loved the different types of characters in this novel! This is the reason why I would rather read than watch a movie. There was plenty of thrills, suspense, action, and spice. If you like strong female leads and a hot passionate male then this is the book for you.<br /><br />Irrevocable (Irrevocable, #1) ~5 stars~<br />by Skye Callahan <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1LgN3u1">http://bit.ly/1LgN3u1</a><br />Awesome dark read! Be warned this book may have some triggers for some. This book was a complete twist and turnaround! I did not see anything coming in this book. You will have characters you will love, hate, and not know how to feel about them. For the ending..let me just say it was not a quick throw together..i do not want to give ANY spoilers! Definitely will be reading more from Skye Callahan!<br /><br />A Special Connection ~5 stars~ <br />by Theresa Troutman <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bit.ly/1BKOOxy">http://bit.ly/1BKOOxy</a><br />Another five star read from Theresa Troutman! I have read all of her books now and I have loved all of them! There is something about her writing style that brings you in and fall in love with her work. I cannot wait until she has more wonderful novel to read. If you like a good romance with a little hotness added to it, A Special Connection is the book to read!<br /><br />~Indie Impressions</span>
