<div id="review_1295305319" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1295305319" />
    <a title="Gloria Herrera for As You Wish Reviews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14588166-gloria-herrera-for-as-you-wish-reviews"><img alt="Gloria Herrera for As You Wish Reviews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447921019p2/14588166.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1295305319?book_show_action=true">May 31, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gloria Herrera for As You Wish Reviews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gloria Herrera for As You Wish Reviews" href="/user/show/14588166-gloria-herrera-for-as-you-wish-reviews">Gloria Herrera for As You Wish Reviews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1295305319" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11429979124659705579">Fifteen amazingly hot stories all bundled up for us at a special price. What a treat! I spent hours reading these stories and I have to admit, I loved them. Here is my review of two of the stories just to give you an idea.<br/><br/>Royal Blood (Royal Blood #1) by Amity Cross <br/><br/>The warning from the author has to be reiterated. If you are looking for a sweet sentimental and rosy romance, this is not a book for you. This book is meant for readers who love to read about the darkness in our souls, the evil side </span>
  <span id="freeText11429979124659705579" style="display:none">Fifteen amazingly hot stories all bundled up for us at a special price. What a treat! I spent hours reading these stories and I have to admit, I loved them. Here is my review of two of the stories just to give you an idea.<br /><br />Royal Blood (Royal Blood #1) by Amity Cross <br /><br />The warning from the author has to be reiterated. If you are looking for a sweet sentimental and rosy romance, this is not a book for you. This book is meant for readers who love to read about the darkness in our souls, the evil side we control and hide, the side that sometimes recognizes the underbelly of society exists and it is not pretty. All that said, that underbelly of society has some great stories to tell and if you can stomach it, you will be challenged, thrilled and will be emotionally impacted.<br /><br />Right from the start we know Mercy is running away from someone. She has dyed her hair to change her appearance, lost weight, and now has a tough exterior that says "do not f**k with me". All in all, she is still a beautiful woman, just unattainable. Working at a seedy bar owned by the motorcycle gang known as Royal Blood is about all she can do to keep herself alive. The pay is good and in cash. No social security numbers to give, no ID to flash, just do the job and survive.<br /><br />"X" is man few can look in the eye. He is a gorgeous man, but evil, danger, and death are projected vibes everyone feels when they are in the same room with him. He is the "hitman" for the gang, and no one messes with him. The fact that he is instantly attracted to Mercy just makes life complicated for both of them.<br /><br />Secrets abound in this story. This is the first book in this series. It is a gripping story of fear, death and survival. It is raw and without embellishment. Sometimes it takes a broken soul to recognize the darkness we have to deal with within ourselves. Maybe two broken souls can heal each other.<br /><br />"Darkness clung to my mind as I struggled to the surface, trying to drag me down. It would be so much easier to just give in."<br /><br />My Last Dom by Deanndra Hall<br /><br />This is a poignant story. Kimberly loved her husband and stood by him for years. Raised her son, took care of her home, and one day, her husband totally destroyed her world by walking out on her. It wasn't so much that he divorced her, it was that he crushed her spirit on his way out. Now she is errantly surviving without a Dom or a purpose. <br /><br />Jaz is also divorced his story is a bit different, but with the same consequences. He also carries with him a dark secret he cannot easily share with others. He also is existing and hoping to find a partner to his Dom ... a submissive who will also love and cherish him.<br /><br />This is their journey. For a D/s relationship to work, there must be trust and honesty. In Deandra Hall's consummate storytelling skills, she weaves us a story of despair and redemption. Forget what you think you know about this lifestyle. This is the story that best defines how unique the D/s relationship is. Each couple is its own world. Each couple controls the parameters of the relationship. <br />I love this story! Kim and Jaz deserve their HEA.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11429979124659705579" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


