<div id="review_1304546178" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1304546178" />
    <a title="G" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26554926-g"><img alt="G" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1304546178?book_show_action=true">Jun 10, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="G" class="user" itemprop="url" name="G" href="/user/show/26554926-g">G</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1304546178" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10651073673368653295">I received an ARC of this book for an honest review.<br/><br/>I&apos;m a big fan of anthologies because t’s usually a good way to discover new authors work and to get a lot of books for a really good price. Although there is always the possibility that some of the books are just meh. This anthology was good, lots of freaking hot stories with very interesting characters. A few of the books I did not quite like, or felt much of a pull to, but overall a fantastic offering.A few that were part of a series or the s</span>
  <span id="freeText10651073673368653295" style="display:none">I received an ARC of this book for an honest review.<br /><br />I'm a big fan of anthologies because t’s usually a good way to discover new authors work and to get a lot of books for a really good price. Although there is always the possibility that some of the books are just meh. This anthology was good, lots of freaking hot stories with very interesting characters. A few of the books I did not quite like, or felt much of a pull to, but overall a fantastic offering.A few that were part of a series or the start of one which is good as a few of the stories had secondary characters I was interested in to discover what their lives held as well.<br /><br />Royal Blood by Amity Cross 4.5 stars<br /><br />The first book in the anthology and this really gripped me. The characters were strong and flawed, the writing was superb and I was l left thinking if all the books are like this then it’s a winner. Mercy is a woman on the run after the murder of her family. She finds herself changed after this and after attempting to get revenge, her fate is sealed. She walks into a bar for a job, and meets X. X is a man tormented, tortured to become the hit man of the Royal Blood MC. He’s determined to complete one last job, that will bring him enough money to get out. His job unfortunately bring him into direct contact with the woman behind the bar. <br />Mercy knows X is dangerous, but the attraction pulls and she dances with his fire until she finds herself into a tight situation. With everyone playing a game, and no one telling the truth when information comes to light that X needs, he will trust the the woman he’s taken will help him find those answers his mind cannot remember. Brilliant, dark and raw. <br /><br />Angel Falling by Audrey Carlan 4 stars<br /><br />Rich businesswoman and hot cowboy builder. What a great story. I was pleasantly surprised with this story. The characters were well written, the romance believable and the friendships funny and outrageous. Aspen and Hank really hit it off, even as they worried about how the relationship would progress once he has to leave her home after the accident that saves her life and his job on her building is complete. With family pressures around and friends , will Aspen give into her heart of her head?<br />A heart -warming steamy story that will keep you reading from beginning to end. I loved these characters, a vulnerable woman finds a man who’s strong enough to take her on. A tale that will leave you wanting more from the author. <br /><br />Escaping Me by Cat Mason 3.5 stars<br /><br />Daisy Shayne is a planner, she knows where her life is going. With summer approaching, her fiancée Landon asks her to accompany him on a tour with his brother’s band Shaft. Meeting the band is nothing like she expected especially when Grayson comes on to her, and he’s the fiancée brother. <br />It all goes to the dogs in less than a week when it seemed while Daisy was planning for one life, Landon has some mega secrets he’s been holding out on her. Not surprisingly she gets involved with Gayson, a bit quick in my book but hey it’s a book, and it’s a rock band. The other characters in here were funny, quirky. All about the sex, the bacon and the women. Grayson is a bit of a prick in the beginning , but rallies round when Daisy’s life goes to hell. He knows what he wants and goes after it no holds bared.<br /><br />Releasing Rage by Cynthia Sax 4 stars<br /><br />Gosh I loved this book. So much I read it more than once. I love a strong female lead, one who will give her all for her man and I loved Joan here. Joan, the singular female engineer on a battle station surrounded by sorry excuses for men; and the cyborgs that fight for humans in eradicating the Mantidae, an Alien life form. When she’s paired with a C model Cyborg, she’s overjoyed. She wanted to be paired with one since her rescue as a child, but when she meets Rage she realizes that the other engineers on the ship are actual scum and she realises how dangerous thy are as they consider the cyborgs to be non-feeling entities.<br />Rage is a cyborg who’s endured much, he’s been tortured by previous handlers. As a C model, he’s primitive as there are newer models that look human; whilst for him it’s obvious he’s not. He has the highest kill rate of all the cyborgs hunting the Mantidae for the humans. When Joan walks into his chambers claiming to be his new engineer, he doesn’t trust her and announces she will not last long as he will end up killing her as humans are all bad. But the more Joan treats him like he’s worth something and cares for him, he realises this female of his is a keeper. <br />This was very good and not wanting to give more away, I’ll say the writing was fantastic and the main characters were heart- warming, I loved the secondary cyborgs characters and found myself wondering If they will all have their HEA. So will be keeping an eye out for their stories as well.<br /><br />My Last Dom by Deandre Hall 5 stars<br /><br />I loved, absolutely loved this book. Kimmie’s suffering from a broken heart/spirit since her husband left her for a younger woman a few years ago, after confessing that he never loved her. This is especially hard as he was her Dom all this time, and this confession breaks her leaving her feeling worthless and in pain. She self-medicates by being a pain slut in the dungeon she visits. He friends tries to help but she doesn’t want it. When she meets Jaz, she connects to him immediately. A Dominant with a difference in her world. He makes her feel again and she makes him complete and understand his fears as well. <br />Once these two get together the chemistry is so explosive. It makes me want a man like him, I was practically throbbing when she was. The writing of this story was superb , it was like being there. I also loved that the characters were a bit older than the norm. A tale of the bonding process, the characters are human and struggles with their own fears and attempt to conquer them with each other. It’s not all roses as they were parts in there that were hard to read when there was regression.<br /><br />Perpetual Love by Jamie Salisbury 3 stars<br /><br />This one wasn’t really my cup of tea, but it was an okay story. It was good to see the lead female Anne being such a strong woman, as the timeframe this was based on this would have been unusual. I liked how these characters grew together, before getting together but that would have been common at that time too. The issues with her father and Joe young were the only bit that surprised me as those seemed to have been brushed aside, so it felt a bit incomplete.<br /><br />Letting Go, Anchored hearts by J.M Witt 3.5 stars<br /><br />I wasn’t sure how to take this one, it seemed a bit choppy. It starts with Cassidy and her friend Holly meeting at the bar with their respective boyfriends. When Cassidy man at the moment introduces her to James, she’s attracted to him but as she’s with Dan it’s not pursued. After a shoot- out at a bar and Holly dies, Cassidy is heart broken by her friend’s death. When her brother breaks the news that the owner of the bar was involved, it’s even more painful as James was the owner.<br />After they meet again, due to a little wrangling from James family at a party she’s organizing, the heat is still there and they get together. James is very take charge, and sometimes just a bit too much. Like when he has his people re-decorate her bedroom without her approval. It was interesting as the story is told from both POV, though sometimes they would be talking about the same event, but it seemed so different and it threw me off a few times. Very descriptive, and loads of music references which just annoyed me. A few silly sentences , and although she knows he’s rich and has money when they picture gets into the papers she gets a bit angsty. Again wanted to slap the silly out of both of them. <br /><br />The Descendant by Kelley Grealis 3.5 stars<br /><br />I was not expecting the story I got with this book. It seemed to start off one way then turned into something completely different . It required paying attention to get the story straight as well.<br />Allison is currently having a body crisis, having dreams of a garden that calms her, but throws the rest of her moods off. She’s suffering from hot flushes and cold sweats and the doctors can’t find anything wrong. Matt her husband is being very supportive of her and what she’s going through. When they get in an accident after a party one night, everything really gets strange as Allison wakes up and is now told t’s three years later and Matt is dead. She no longer lives where she was and has cut all her friends off, and now apparently has a new boyfriend Vincent.<br />It gets strange here on in, as Vincent reveals that she’s a descendant of the first Vampire and must either be turned or killed. A bit of biblical and paranormal twist to throw this story into another realm. When she’s turned against her will, and it’s revealed to her Matt is alive. Allison decides it’s time to take a step away and discover what and who’s being honest with her.<br />The writing is good, story moves at a good pace, but it takes a while to get into it.<br /><br />Rescued, Three’s allowed by Laura Harner 4 stars<br /><br />I loved this book. When Graeme is awakened to go check out a domestic at a gas station, the last thing he expects is to find the woman who he pushed into another mans’ arms years ago. Elizabeth Ashford has a crazy husband after her, when she escapes him at a rest room and a stranger tries to help her she never expect to come face to face with the man she’s always loved. Michael Enwright tries to do a good deed and gets his car totalled and shot up. <br />When Graeme offers his house as protection for Lizzie, Michael tags along as he’s into security and has made a connection with the woman he’s saved. When these three get together, a few home truths come out and they all fall in love. But it’s not all roses as Lizzie crazy husband tries to ensure if he doesn’t have her no one will. The characters in this were great, attraction between them is honest and although it’s almost like instalove, there is a back story to Lizzie and Graeme so this worked well.<br /><br />Man On (Black Jack gentlemen) by Liz Crowe 3.5 stars<br /><br />A story of one man discovering himself and an older one trying to convince himself he’s worthy of change and second chances. This book is set in the world of sports, Nicco is bisexual but has been outed as gay by his ex-wife, so his soccer career is basically over in Europe. He moves to America as part of the Black Jacks a trial squad. He meets young Parker, a man who’s recently gotten out from under his parents thumb and they intentions for him to go to college, marry a nice girl and produce the requisite 2.5kids. He rebels, joins the football world and after setting eyes on Nicco he realises that although he likes the ladies, he has a thing for guys. After an incident at a club, they resort to keeping up appearances until Nicco decides he wants change and, when the two eventually get together the sparks fly. <br />The pace of the story was good, and the POV was from both men as well as from Rafe, the Co-manager of the team. This was a bit different, but it did give us a wider view of what the team was about. I was only unhappy as the time flipped so fast, it seemed we missed the relationship growing. The author did a good job of portraying what athletes who do come out have to face and the personal devils that sometimes haunt them. <br /><br />Relent, Sydney Storm MC by Nina Levine 4 stars<br /><br />A new MC series by Nina Levine, this book features Evie and Kick. Kick is a member of the MC Storm, he got into the club as a young man, and they have been like family to him. He’s done some bad things for his Pres and the club. Due to where he is, he gave up on Evie the woman he still loves. These two grew up together and Kick was always there for Evie until three years ago when they were in a relationship and he walked away because of something that was said by a mutual friend.<br />After the death of the part 3 of their friendship, Evie and Kick connect again. She knows he’s done things in the club he’s not proud of, but she also knows that she still loves this man and he completes a part of her that no one has been able to. Second chances at love story, the characters are fleshed out and it was easy to get involved in their story and see where the relationship was going to go and end up. Loved it<br />A good story, there is a lot of interplay between the members of the clubs and the various family members of both Kick and Evie. It makes you wonder about what their individual stories are. The chemistry between these two is hot, the sex scenes are amazing and I want to know where the handcuffs went. <br /><br />Make mine a Cowboy by Sandy Sullivan 3.5 stars<br /><br />A really feel good cowboy romance story. The story of the author who goes to a romance book conference only to fall in love with her very own cowboy. Mesa is an author who’s currently having a slump in her writing, when she goes to a book conference and goes for a drive, she never expects to be stranded and rescued by her very own cowboy. Not only that there’s three of them identical. But she’s only got eyes for Joel.<br />Joel is one of the nine Young brothers, one of the triplets. These boys are hot, hard bodied and very individual. He’s interested in Mesa, but is convinced this will just be a brief affair as she stays on their dude ranch whilst doing some hands on research. Unfortunately the heart wants what the heart wants, and he quickly discovers that he wants her forever. <br />Loved this book and I’m looking forward to seeing the rest of the brothers books.<br /><br />Seal under Covers by Sharon Hamilton 3.5 stars<br /><br />I loved Military stories, and SEALS get me hot. This is the third book in the series, so wasn’t sure if I would miss out on some back story but this held up as a standalone, they were some references to stuff that happened previously, but nothing so great that you felt you missed much. I wanted this book to be so much better, so I was a little disappointed that it didn’t grab me as I was hoping for. I didn’t get into the characters that much and sometimes it felt a bit flat. <br />Gina is an undercover cop trying to get information to put Carlos, the Scorpions leader behind bars, to do this she’s using Mia Guzman to get close. As the female undercover agent, the team she’s working with includes her ex Sam- not good news for her as he wants to get back with her and she wants him gone. Gina seems a little lost in this story, I don’t get much from her character and I found myself just thinking she’s quite bland. The author tries but she didn't resound with me as a detective who should be undercover.<br />Armando is Mia’s big brother and a member of the SEALS. He comes back from training only to find his sister is back with the bad news guys. He is a character that was a bit fleshed out, there was more to him. He has a thing for Gina, but is certain she’s lying to him, but he never finds out what until the very end. He and Gina get together, and the sex scenes are great, so big plus here. <br />Didn't enjoy this as much as I wanted unfortunately.<br /><br />Irrevocable by Skye Callahan 4.5 stars<br /><br />A dark and gritty read that pulls at the gut. This book may be a trigger for some readers, so caution to be taken with this read. <br />Awakening in hell, a woman becomes Silver. Not sure how she got there, she taken from a situation between five men to just one who will own her body and soul. She’s handed over like a dog to a man she must call master, if she wants to survive, but now she’s told she needs to forget her old life and be what she is now- a slave.<br />A strong character, Silver will not break. She fights to retain herself even when she is raped repeatedly, and assaulted. She should be broken like all the other girls in the situation, but she’s not. <br />Kirk, the man she’s given to. At the beginning I hated his character, but he changed my opinion of him as the story goes on. It’s hard to say much without giving away the story here, but suffice to say,there were some twists in this book I didn't see coming.<br />The characters in this book were all fleshed out, and evoked emotions in me that made me stop reading at points and just breathe to continue. A good read, with all the requisite darkness you would expect to find in this type of book<br /><br />A Special Connection by Theresa Troutman 4 stars<br /><br />New Adult story of first loves and first times. A sweet emotional story of best friends who discover their love for each other. Jake, Rick and Samantha are best friends . Samantha and Rick are a couple, Sam is the brain, whilst Rick is the budding sport star. Jake is the storyteller here, and he’s had it bad. An accident that killed his parents and damages his leg, has left him certain no woman will be interested in him. When a kiss from Sam has him thinking, maybe the love he feels for her isn't just as a friend but perhaps more. This is one of the least steamy books in the anthology, but the scenes we do get are well written. This is a book that stays with you.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10651073673368653295" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


