        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1298709318" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3048557171028639051">Royal Blood by Amity Cross<br/>This was a really good MC book and with the mystery and suspense added in made it even better, oh and also the hot exchanges between Mercy and X was good too. How the author ended this book has left me wanting to read more books in this series. All in all I have just found a new author to add books to my ever growing list of books to read. <br/><br/>Angel Falling by Audrey Carlan<br/>I&apos;ve read several books by this author and this is another great book. I mean what else course you ask</span>
  <span id="freeText3048557171028639051" style="display:none">Royal Blood by Amity Cross<br />This was a really good MC book and with the mystery and suspense added in made it even better, oh and also the hot exchanges between Mercy and X was good too. How the author ended this book has left me wanting to read more books in this series. All in all I have just found a new author to add books to my ever growing list of books to read. <br /><br />Angel Falling by Audrey Carlan<br />I've read several books by this author and this is another great book. I mean what else course you ask for with a hot and sexy cowboy out to win the heart of a sexy powerful business woman in New York. Of course within all the sexy times with Hank and Aspen is a great story of over coming two people from different social circles to show their love can over come anything. I just love all the characters in the story and how they made the story complete.<br /><br />Escaping Me by Cat Mason<br />This is a great rocker book and had me laughing with the funny things that the guys from Shaft would say. This books is HOT at times with a few sad parts worked into make it a really great story. I'll by looking forward to reading more of the authors books.<br /><br />Releasing Rage by Cynthia Sax<br />This story was completely different compared tot he other books that I have read. I like the strong female character that was in the story in the middle of a mostly male population. In all this was a very interesting story.<br /><br />My Last Dom by Deanndra Hall<br />Another awesome book by Deanndra Hall. She always finds a way to pull every emotion out of me when i read her books. She makes you laugh, makes you cry and then you just want to scream and throw the book. And this book doesn't lack in any of that and also add some super hot sex and its perfect. I completely love Jasper AKA Jax, Mr. hot sexy dome that completely stole my heart in this book. I can't wait for her next book to come out to read.<br /><br />Perpetual Love by Jamie Salisbury<br />This was such a sweet love story with a little suspense. I loved the main female character Anne. She always said what was on her mind and was a spitfire. This was not the usual type of book that i read, but rather enjoyed reading something different.<br /><br />Letting Go by JM Witt<br />This was suck a good book with a lot of suspense and romance with a little hint of BDSM in the story. James is one hot alpha male that totally takes your breath away. I was going crazy at the ending with the cliffhanger and wanted to know more. Can't wait to read the next book in this series.<br /><br />The Descendant by Kelley Grealis<br />The start of this book was a little confusing to me. You don't get the full picture till you get over half way through. Other than that part it was a different side to a vampire story.It was different having the story set in the same state I live in Ohio and Lake Erie.<br /><br />Rescued by Laura Harner<br />I really enjoyed this book and finding out there is more than this book makes me want to get the others and read them too. The mixture of love, suspense and tragedy was the perfect combo that kept you so involved in the story. This was a quick read but had a lot put into a good story in that short time. I can't wait to read more books in this series or others the author has written.<br /><br />Man On by Liz Crowe<br />Another great book by Liz Crowe. This story shows the struggle of one coming to terms of his true sexuality and another finding out he is able to love again. Really a great story and can't wait to red the rest in the series.<br /><br />Relent by Nina Levine<br />WOW, this was a really good MC Book. Evie and Kick what a match. Kick is a hot alpha male biker torn between being loyal to his club and wanting to be with the woman he loves. This was not just another MC story, but a deep vision like an episode of Sons of Anarchy. I felt like I was watching this story instead of reading it. I could imagine all the places and people in this story with how well the author described everything making me feel like I was in the story. I will be adding a few more books from this author to my reading list.<br /><br />Make Mine a Cowboy by Sandy Sullivan<br />This was suck a sweet and sexy cowboy story. I liked how Mesa was a romance writer of cowboy romance and falls for a cowboy. Joel completely swept me off my feet. Hot and sweet as pie cowboy with all the southern manners of a gentleman. I really enjoyed this book and will be looking into more books by this author.<br /><br />In all this was really a great collection of books all in one. You get such a wide variety of different types of romance stories and get a chance to reading something that you might not have before.<br /><br /></span>
